          "href": "https://www.w3schools.com/c_structs.php",
          "title": ""
        }
      ],
      "text": "A union is similar to a struct in that it can store members of different data types.",
      "html": "<p>A <strong>union</strong> is similar to a <a href=\"c_structs.php\">struct</a> in that it can store members of different data types.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "However, there are some differences:",
      "html": "<p>However, there are some differences:</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "structs",
          "href": "https://www.w3schools.com/c_structs.php",
          "title": ""
        }
      ],
      "text": "Most of the time, you will use structs instead of unions, as it can store and access multiple values at the same time, which is more common in everyday programs.",
      "html": "<p>Most of the time, you will use <a href=\"c_structs.php\">structs</a> instead of unions, as it can store and access multiple values at the same time, which is more common in everyday programs.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "However, unions are useful when you only need to store one of several possible types at a time, and you want to save memory.",
      "html": "<p>However, unions are useful when you only need to store one of several possible types at a time, and you want to save memory.</p>"
    },
