      "text": "Access Union Members",
      "level": "h2"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "And just like with structs, to access members of a Union, use the dot . syntax.",
      "html": "<p>And just like with structs, to access members of a Union, use the dot <code>.</code> \nsyntax.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "Important: Since all members share the same memory, changing one will affect the others. Only the last assigned member holds a valid value:",
      "html": "<p><strong>Important:</strong> Since all members share the same memory, changing one will affect the others. Only the <strong>last assigned member</strong> holds a valid value:</p>"
